Git notes is the substrate. If git can do it, we don't wrap it.
If git can't do it, we think twice before building it.

Story: branch-scoped notes needed a way to merge. Instead of writing
a merge algorithm, we used git notes merge — a built-in command with
conflict strategies (ours/theirs/union/cat_sort_uniq). The entire
branch command is 40 lines because git does the hard work.

The constraint 'bash and git only' is the hard version of this value.
The value is softer: prefer the git-native way even when a custom
solution would be slightly more ergonomic. The git way composes with
the rest of the ecosystem. The custom way doesn't.
